    <item>
      <title>Interactive Map - Patch 1/title>
      <pubDate>Saturday, 16 September 2023</pubDate>
      <description>
	&lt;h1&gt;Sorry for the issues!!&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;p&gt;The release build did not work as intended, so this patch should fix any major Interactive Map crashes!&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;FIXES&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;There was a major crash caused by loading into the Map Menu. This crash was caused by unforseen logic in the production (public release) build variant. What is currently live should those fix issue!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
      </description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Interactive Map - Major Update</title>
      <pubDate>Friday, 15 September 2023</pubDate>
      <description>
	&lt;h1&gt;New features&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;ADDITIONS&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;A whole new Map Viewer has been added!&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;The Map Viewer can now be interacted with! Select a Map, select a floor of the map, locate cursed items, locate fuse boxes, and find/select rooms with a tap of the finger! Not sure where a room is? Use the dropdown list of rooms. Selecting a room from the dropdown will highlight the room on the Map! Not sure what the room is called? Tap on the image of the room and the dropdown will show the name!&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;You may also use the Map Viewer to visualize the locations of any Fuse Box or Cursed Item!&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added Japanese, Chinese Simplified, Italian, Portuguese, Russian, and Czech translations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;FIXES&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Better information about the equipment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed translations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;FUTURE UPDATES&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;A display, much like the Safehouse Item Shop, that displays extended information about all equipment.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
      </description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Ascension Update - Patch 1</title>
      <pubDate>Thursday, 17 August 2023</pubDate>
      <description>
	&lt;h1&gt;New features&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;ADDITIONS&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added popup of GDPR consent form in titlescreen for EU/UK users&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added link to GDPR consent form in settings for EU/UK users&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added Settings page Font style selection&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added "P.E.T. Classic", "Journal", "Android", "Brick" and "Clean" fonts&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added Hunt data to Ghost information popup.&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added paging between Overview and Tiers in the Evidence information popup&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Added Evidence information page animations&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;FIXES&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Settings page layout.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed translations.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Ghost information popup.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Evidence information popup.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed fonts not fitting.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed some global style issues.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed layout to App Info page.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed layout of Evidence Information for landscape mode.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed all Ghost information's Hunting Data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Evidence information popup fullscreen images.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Landscape fonts.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Evidence Fragment layouts to function better.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Fixed Ghost popup to scale textviews appropriately.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;h1&gt;FUTURE UPDATES&lt;/h1&gt;
	&lt;ul class=&quot;bb_ul&quot;&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Due to the progression system, tools cannot be tested or viewed yet. As more information starts rolling in, the Evidence and Tool information pages will gradually become more complete.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	  &lt;li&gt;Translations for the Czech and Russian languages.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
      </description>
